Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.46,0:00:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they're going to have jets that are faster than the supersonic.\NThey're going to bounce off the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.82,0:00:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank you and Susan,\Nand I want to just state before everybody that I claim you as my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.38,0:00:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The question I have has to do with constant prayer.\NI know I want to heal something around Christianity,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:01:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, and my relationship to God that comes from my childhood,\Nbut my father conditioned us with beliefs from a Christian sect
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.03,0:01:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that was based in revelations and apocalypse and an angry God.\NI was attracted, after I became spiritual for the last 20 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.95,0:01:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was more attracted to godless religions like Buddhism,\Nwhere there wasn't as strong a concept of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.21,0:01:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But through your teachings over the last three years,\NI've realized,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.47,0:01:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen Christianity and God from a new perspective,\Nand I'm grateful for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.39,0:01:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This summer, I've taken a three-month sabbatical to focus on constant prayer\Nand to spend time in the wilderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where I can focus on making it as much a part of my life as possible.\NThe questions I have have to do with the prayer I'm choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.69,0:01:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I took your teachings that I had heard,\Nand I used the prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.61,0:01:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory be to thee, O Lord.\NThy will be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.59,0:02:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I repeated that over and over again.\NAs time went on,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.71,0:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of my life came up before me,\Nand I started to see how much I needed salvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and what I felt as I wanted to switch to the Jesus prayer.\NAnd the Jesus prayer has the statement of,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.04,0:02:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for Lord Jesus Christ,\Nhave mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.55,0:02:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have mercy on me,\Na sinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that didn't feel good to me,\Nso I used the terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.29,0:02:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Jesus Christ,\NI ask your mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.73,0:02:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I repeat that over and over again.\NSo the question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is that an appropriate language to address Christ in a prayer?\NAre you aware of what you call the Brother Lawrence,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the practice of the presence of God by Brother Lawrence?\NNo, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be a good thing to look up,\Nbecause it's really sort of what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.96,0:03:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBrother, it's a very small little booklet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know where you can get any of it.\NIt's the prayer of Brother Lawrence, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NWell, to be constantly conscious and aware of the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NIt's boiled down to its probably most simple form,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lawrence.\NYou know, what should we call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.69,0:03:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lawrence.\NWhat's the word I want?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.14,0:03:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we call it?\NBrother Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.14,0:03:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The practice of the presence of God.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The practice of the presence of God by Brother Lawrence is very famous,\Ntime-honored, and has been used for great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.48,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, if you're looking for something that has been validated by widespread usage,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe practice of the presence of God is the name of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.86,0:04:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThe last question I have about the prayer is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.86,0:04:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as I'm walking down the aisle,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,walking in the wilderness,\Nit starts to take a singing quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.86,0:04:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of like a choir singing the prayer.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.86,0:04:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe because of my childhood and my scrupulosity around Christianity is,\NI don't want that to be a disrespect of the prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.86,0:04:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems to happen naturally and it also feels good as I'm praying.\NSo, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the angelic response.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.12,0:04:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, it's primarily singing in my consciousness and very little just.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.12,0:04:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the angelic.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.44,0:04:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I was doing, was worrying about it.\NIt'd be nice not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the angelic.\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:05:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NAnd I'd like to have a picture with my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAngelic, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NMy question's also about prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing,\NGlory be to Thee, O Lord, Thy will be done,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Jesus prayer,\Nwould it enhance it by having some sort of gratitude towards God,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.43,0:05:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thanking Him or His divinity?\NBeing specific about gratitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I think we're too much interested in the words verbatim.\NI think the overall intention of devotion can be expressed anyway, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think any kind of wording that's comfortable to you, you know?\NIt's the,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the energy with which it resonates.\NThat,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so how the wording I don't think makes that much difference.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.60,0:06:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.71,0:06:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's easier to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, that's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.83,0:06:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOtherwise I get all my weight on my elbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.56,0:06:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NI've been doing the Course in Miracles workbook this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I'm finding at certain lessons, like for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the peace of God.\NThat day, it's like all hell breaks loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.95,0:06:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I feel guilty and I don't know how to work through it.\NWell, you should know what it could have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:07:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Flattened by a truck.\NWell, don't forget, karmic propensities come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, we expect that it's going to be the way we want it to be\Nby praying and asking for a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that your phone bill is going to be paid now and not shut off.\NAnd we think, well, if they shut off my phone, it didn't answer my prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God wants you to know if you don't pay your phone bill,\Nthey're going to shut it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You got the message.\NIt's called pay attention to reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't know whether you're getting an answer to the prayer or not.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.04,0:07:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And to puzzle out the meaning of what you experience next until you understand it.\NAll right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NTuesday night when I was meditating, suddenly the words came up,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ask Dr. Hawkins how you're doing.\NSo and instantly total and complete terror came up to the point where I was almost physically ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.24,0:08:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sensible.\NSo in order to work through the fear, I came up and I'm asking, how am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.29,0:08:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing wonderfully.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.29,0:08:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To get out in front of the audience when you're suffering from anxiety and overcome it, face it, and break it out.\NWhat more could you ask for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.32,0:08:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,True.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.74,0:08:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.28,0:09:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NHi, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Susan.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For the longest time, I've had a problem in terms of a personal connection to divinity, to God.\NAnd I even wrote a book, Struggling to Surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.83,0:09:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave you a copy when I first met you.\NAnd I just recently got it watching a 2002 video about surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.08,0:09:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee, O Lord of God imminent.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.08,0:09:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you explain a little bit more about the connection between, is that like the gateway to God transcendent?\NDon't worry about God transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou don't have to worry about the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.94,0:09:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky's fine the way it is.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You worry about, don't worry anyway.\NWell, I'm not really worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.13,0:09:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just not really.\NGod imminent is identical to what the world considers to be transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, a lot of people call God you, and it's an other, other.\NIt's an other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't realize that, you know, as Christ said, heaven is within you.\NHeaven is within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.44,0:10:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Discover the infinite presence within oneself.\NGod is simultaneously transcendent and imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are merely artifacts of languaging.\NTranscendent and imminent are not contradictory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just different ways of stylizing it and vocabulary.\NBut traditional religion, you know, speaks of God transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.88,0:10:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus said God is, heaven is within you.\NGod is both transcendent and imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.01,0:10:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such an incredible gift to be able to see that, well, I'm not surrendering to something out there, but this bigger piece within myself.\NYeah, it's not an out there-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.17,0:11:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I don't like the term you for God.\NThat's a pronoun, you know, and it's limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.46,0:11:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't such a thing as you God.\NThe closest you can come is to thee, O Lord, to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.93,0:11:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thee is respectful.\NAnd thee implies the recognition of the divinity because that's the only thee that appears, you know, historically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.80,0:11:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, is God transcendent, spoken of respectfully.\NThat's why I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.47,0:11:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You say you, O God, you're making it like two persons, two personalities separated.\NThere's me and then there's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:12:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of a not too evolved kind of comprehension of divinity, you.\NI think that's what 95% of the world gets transcended down to or, you know, what was my understanding of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.20,0:12:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So thank you so much.\NThe ineffable is very hard to put into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,About seven years ago, I was involved in a group of a spiritual teacher.\NI had...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.80,0:12:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Involved in what?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got...\NDoes she have to be closer or further?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.56,0:12:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got real dramatic changes in my life.\NBut about five years ago, I moved away and I lost any contact with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.56,0:13:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to continue my study with the group.\NBut right now, the group, for an outsider like me, looks much more like a sect than the group that it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Same group.\NIt's just you see it differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.91,0:13:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI just see the teacher and the group itself differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.91,0:13:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like a splinter group, yeah?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.91,0:13:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NNo, their attitude to the teacher and her role in the world and their role of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in her teaching and so on.\NIt looks like they're creating a new religion with her being a messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.03,0:13:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The leader of this group.\NThe leader of this group.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.37,0:13:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A new messiah?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.08,0:13:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to redo the calendar.\NMake this year one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just wanted to ask you to calibrate the information coming from her back then and now.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want any names.\NYou hold in mind the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher is over 200, is this?\N240?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.83,0:14:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,500?\N600?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.99,0:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,505?\N510?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,505?\NThat's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A lovingness, right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So basically, I can continue doing the studying.\NSo what's the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.04,0:14:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I can continue doing the studying.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.94,0:14:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She can go through all that now.\NNo, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.94,0:14:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Her enemies.\NHer enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Her enemies.\NHer enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Her enemies.\NHer enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Her enemies.\NOh, that's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.27,0:14:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.27,0:14:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But my energy is remaining high.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.27,0:14:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's .\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're cultizing around her.\NThe other people in the group are cultizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.36,0:14:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're cultizing.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.80,0:14:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut I can't go in the details of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.60,0:15:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\NThe teacher feels all right at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.92,0:15:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody ask me another question if you don't mind.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.04,0:15:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.\NMm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.56,0:15:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to ask a question, and I also want to put it in a context, so that the question\NSo that the question becomes clearer. My question is if being
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.98,0:15:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Being and feeling grateful\Nallows
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For grace to flow down. Yes onto one gratitude gratitude\NThe context is I have a business to run a business to run
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.92,0:16:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah business, yeah\NI
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.22,0:16:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Noticed that whenever I think of promoting my business\NMarketing anything of the sort nothing works
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as I start working on myself by addressing by working by reading a book like this by\NListening a tape that you have as long as I step away from business and concentrate on developing my conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.88,0:16:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah consciousness and you attract then everything works. Yeah. Yeah\NWhat I'm true, however, I still have a business to so I'm still attached
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.77,0:16:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit. So what I'm trying to do is I'm trying to ask people for testimonials\NWhen they get help through my business
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, that doesn't happen\NSo I'm trying to see within myself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.04,0:17:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is something that I need to undo or get better with on my own so that it happens\NMeaning am I not grateful enough myself that they don't feel grateful to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.87,0:17:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you ask them for this?\NYes, them for a testimonial. Yeah, if they have what's a relief of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.96,0:17:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the result you feel better. Could you give us just the result of what?\NI'm a refrigerator. What is it? I'm a doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and so they come to me because they have pain and so I help them with it. Are you looking for testimonials?\NYeah, I wouldn't know as illicit them would not even bother
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.14,0:17:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.74,0:17:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what what furthers your\NPractice is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.80,0:17:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Word of mouth. Yeah, that's that's personally where my\Nfeeling is yes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.22,0:18:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I wouldn't ask them for testimonials because things would really happen on their own if I'm getting yeah\NYeah, that's what I'm thinking too
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it happens spontaneously, right? Yeah\NThank you very much. I know from experience. Yeah, mm-hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.10,0:18:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you do all that you can to the best of your ability\NAnd the energy of that radiates out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.26,0:18:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then other people hear of it, and they send somebody,\Nand they do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then your practice grows and grows.\NAnd you have to run away to Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.02,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Out in the country.\NHiding in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.81,0:18:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gosh.\NI'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.66,0:18:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to look into the eye.\NIt's a real camera, so look into the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.62,0:18:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.44,0:19:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange things happen on this planet, Lord.\NI'm reporting back that strangeness predominates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.68,0:19:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great, yeah.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.10,0:19:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHello, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.74,0:19:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, I want to say thank you with all my heart and soul\Nfor your teachings and for your devotion to your students.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I have a question about the student-teacher energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a field of consciousness,\Na consciousness that I sense between you and all of us as your students.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.71,0:19:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And at times, it arises within me an awareness of your presence.\NAnd sometimes it arises as the hearing of the Kyrie music spontaneously just arises within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.21,0:20:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I sense that you in us, your presence is with me.\NAnd I would just like you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.83,0:20:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe comment on that phenomena and your sense of your accessibility to all of us in this plane and when you are around.\NI pray every night to be a servant of everyone here, to be a servant of God, to be a servant of these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.15,0:20:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I give gratitude, I thank God for the gift to be able to be what I am.\NI am to the students, you know, that to me is a great gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.12,0:20:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I told you, my obligation is to God, my fellow man and myself.\NAnd my fellow man is that as a teacher, just as I was the best physician I could be, to the fullest extent I could be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.80,0:21:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the best hermit I could be to the degree I could be a hermit for a while.\NAnd now I am back in the world in this particular function.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.45,0:21:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do hold all of them in mind and pray for them.\NAnd I pray for the spiritual evolution of everyone here present because they are indeed my blessing and their gift, God's gift to me to be able to serve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.60,0:21:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSo you may be picking up the energy of the prayer itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.31,0:21:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that I hear your voice in my head at times.\NThat would be the way the prayer is going to cross to you, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel that that will be with me for all my days and beyond.\NYes, it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.17,0:21:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so.\NGod bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.49,0:21:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank God for you.\NBlessing me by that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.56,0:21:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NYou make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.97,0:22:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my honor to know you.\NPicture.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there we go.\NVery good, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She picks up the energy of the prayer.\NSomething I heard you say in a recent interview that really stood out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.11,0:22:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If I heard you correctly, you said that we have to master the world before we can transcend it.\NAnd I just wondered what you meant by that, because I think maybe I've been trying to transcend it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.25,0:22:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you have mastered it.\NYou see its value, and its value.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.28,0:23:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To master the world really is to see its value.\NAs a teaching tool, having learned all you can from the world, there's no further need for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.80,0:23:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big toy, a big whirling toy.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.21,0:23:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fun toy.\NIt serves its purpose for a period, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.54,0:23:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we go on to other dimensions, you know.\NThis is not the ultimate dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.54,0:23:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We go on to other dimensions.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.12,0:23:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I had started to understand the whole idea of karmic unity.\NAnd the notion of the every hair on your head being counted, isn't that the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.62,0:24:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing as what?\NI don't know what karmic unity means.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.02,0:24:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What does karmic unity mean?\NWell, the idea that everything leaves a karmic trace, and then, I don't know, you float in the ocean according to your karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.21,0:24:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, everything leaves, yes.\NEverything leaves a trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.21,0:24:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.\NRenewable forever, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's my understanding of karma.\NYeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.21,0:24:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that exists.\NSo then the idea of the hair on the head is also...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.21,0:24:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything exists, everything that ever happens leaves a permanent track for all time, for eternity.\NTherefore, you really don't want to make too bad of a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.63,0:24:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people are going to be reading it centuries from now.\NThey'll say, oh, that one there, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.63,0:24:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what she did, right?\NOh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.63,0:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I pray for mercy, right?\NIt leaves a permanent track.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.63,0:24:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBut it's the same idea, just a different wording then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.63,0:24:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.63,0:25:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that exists emits an energy, including all events, personages, decisions, options.\NAnd that leaves a karmic pattern, a track.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.72,0:25:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what we call about our inherited karmic propensities.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.92,0:25:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.36,0:25:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going as fast as I can.\NMy Widow Wicks can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.43,0:25:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going as fast as my Widow Wicks can win.\NI've been suffering from depression for like 15 years or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.67,0:25:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I'm trying to search for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.67,0:26:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't think the cause is like, I don't believe it's like sugar, like you just say\Nbefore.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.67,0:26:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She's suffering from depression.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.70,0:26:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She has been for years.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.85,0:26:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've been treating with a doctor?\NWith what?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.85,0:26:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been treating with a doctor?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.85,0:26:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I am an antidepressant right now.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.85,0:26:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NAntidepressants.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.85,0:26:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She's on antidepressants.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.85,0:26:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it helping?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.01,0:26:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NBut I would like to, like, get a deeper healing or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.40,0:26:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.40,0:26:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.40,0:26:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the wisdom to accept that which you cannot change.\NThe wisdom to change the things you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.74,0:26:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The wisdom to know the difference.\NSo you do all you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.74,0:26:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're responsible for the effort but not the result.\NAnd many of these depressive things come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.74,0:26:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you stopped eating sugar and sweets.\NDid you try that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.74,0:26:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.06,0:26:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo you've tried the antidepressants.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.06,0:26:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.06,0:26:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.06,0:26:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.16,0:26:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.16,0:26:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.27,0:27:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.27,0:27:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.27,0:27:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've tried the easy ones like functional hypoglycemia and all those kind of things.\NThen you may have to just wait it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.46,0:27:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So these depressions tend to run their course.\NYou may run 10, 15 years and then disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.60,0:27:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just maintain whatever level you need to keep the dopamine, to keep the serotonin\Nlevel up in the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.60,0:27:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's genetic generally.\NAnd you do what you can during the period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.85,0:27:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When that's necessary.\NIn the meantime, you add to it all you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.85,0:27:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI've been doing a course in miracles and all of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.85,0:27:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You do everything else you can do.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.48,0:27:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Using alternate health.\NEverything from acupuncture to who knows what will help.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.48,0:27:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things are worth a trial run.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.48,0:27:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know which one is going to be good.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.58,0:27:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying acupuncture and lots of things.\NSo you're doing what you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.58,0:27:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.58,0:27:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.12,0:27:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.12,0:27:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.12,0:28:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.12,0:28:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.12,0:28:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.12,0:28:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.88,0:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.88,0:28:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're doing what you can do.\NIt's better than being in denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.61,0:28:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to face it.\NDo what you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.13,0:28:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than be in denial.\NAnd then some other solution will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.77,0:28:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.\NTake more vitamin B3.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.80,0:28:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut out sugar and sweets.\NTry acupuncture.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.80,0:28:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Try jogging.\NGod knows what will help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.24,0:28:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.85,0:28:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI have suffered from headaches for about a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.85,0:28:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Headaches?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.41,0:28:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I have epilepsy.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.56,0:28:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Epilepsy.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.34,0:29:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've been to a neurologist, and the second one has made the headaches a bit better.\NInstead of every day, they're probably about five days a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.28,0:29:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NAnd I've read that you suffered with migraine headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.18,0:29:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I was curious on what you did to pass that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.53,0:29:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything under the sun, including acupuncture.\NAcupuncture helped everything, but it didn't cure the migraine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.89,0:29:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had pins and everything.\NI did the whole thing, moxie combustion, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.95,0:29:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It had cured my ulcer, you know, first treatment or second treatment.\NIt didn't do anything for my migraine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.39,0:29:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, but I think everyone is different.\NImitrex came along, and it was like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.76,0:29:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I took a half an Imitrex, and like magic, it disappeared.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.96,0:29:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, they have me on Zomeg.\NIt's a nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.98,0:30:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nose spray that I take when I feel the headache coming on.\NAnd then I also have what they call chronic headaches that are not considered migraines.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.33,0:30:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Cluster headaches, yeah.\NAll right, so you have to, everything's physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.23,0:30:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So you handle it on all three levels, and then you wait it out,\Nand a lot of these things you'll grow out of.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.73,0:30:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.73,0:30:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you just told me.\NMost of the things I had when I was young were all gone, bye-bye, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.19,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get them until I was older.\NThat's what's so bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.91,0:30:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.51,0:30:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't get any of this.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.99,0:30:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.77,0:30:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't old enough to get them yet.\NAnd my own personal experience, middle age was the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.21,0:30:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't one thing after another.\NI mean, it was a wonder I survived at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.79,0:30:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pass the migraines, or do you still get them?\NThe migraines still will recur periodically if the weather's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.63,0:30:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So weather can affect migraines.\NIf the weather comes on, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.37,0:30:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I live in Texas, so I've heard that.\NSo right now, I'm not eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.89,0:30:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm eating chocolate, because you can see it's sucking in.\NI don't want to kind of put anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.92,0:31:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, well, that's a belief system, and you can negate it.\NSo I've been negating it, but I don't want to push my luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.98,0:31:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've heard that.\NWhen the barometric pressure is dropping, it's not a great time to indulge in chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.04,0:31:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've heard that acupuncture has healed some people of epilepsy.\NHas what?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.28,0:31:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Healed people.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.70,0:31:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of wonderful things can be done.\NAnd, of course, there's different acupuncturists with greater and lesser skills, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.34,0:31:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,like any other physician.\NHow do you know which one's good and which one's bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.56,0:31:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you just work on it.\NYou try your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.98,0:31:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You go by reputation.\NYou use kinesiology if you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.20,0:31:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou say, this doctor has capacity to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.36,0:31:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, no.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.42,0:31:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NIt's so lovely to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.92,0:31:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You too.\NHuman beings are fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.60,0:31:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonder how we stay alive.\NI just marvel that we've survived it all, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.24,0:32:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think of all the afflictions that can hit you in one lifetime,\Nthat you know about, and the ones that you didn't know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.65,0:32:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe other day, we're rounding a bend, and Susan's driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.04,0:32:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're out in the country, a sharp turn,\Nand coming right at us at a breakneck speed, right in our lane,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.35,0:32:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is a guy just dying to have a head-on, I guess.\NI mean, you know, totally unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.94,0:32:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Minding your own business.\NWent to church that morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.84,0:32:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on the bed, and here's a maniac coming right at you, dead on,\Nright in your lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.64,0:32:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in your lane.\NGod knows what.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.49,0:32:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Very scary.\NI didn't have time to be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.37,0:32:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over before I got a chance.\NHappy 80th year.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.05,0:32:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, indeed.\NMy question, is the enlightenment level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.62,0:33:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the level where there's no thinking, thoughtlessness, no mind,\Nand is it also the level at which you're released
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.42,0:33:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from personal karma?\NI don't want to answer about personal karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.76,0:33:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's karma at different levels,\Nand different consequences on different levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.28,0:33:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can go beyond the karma of this level,\Nbut you're still stuck with the karmic propensities of humanness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.88,0:33:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and et cetera, see?\NWhat was the first question?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.48,0:33:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is enlightenment the same as the level at which the thinking ceases?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.80,0:33:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes silent.\NThere is instead, in the high 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.62,0:34:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,an exquisite joyfulness, an ecstasy.\NThere then comes a bliss and an infinite state of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.74,0:34:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The peace of God, it's unmistakable.\NYou realize when you go into it, you recognize the peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.47,0:34:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Timeless, infinite.\NAnd without thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember any thought, no.\NYou also can, this is in Sikpat 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.30,0:34:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you can also leave the world at that point,\Nand you're aware that you could leave if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.26,0:34:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody to wish it.\NSo I suppose there's more karmic propensities than anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.54,0:34:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,whether one will continue to survive.\NBut there is a strong desire to leave the world at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.18,0:34:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean.\NIt's an option, with the door standing open, invitationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.12,0:35:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, oh, I forget, probably the majority of people at 600 leave, do.\NAnd that's why there's hardly anybody beyond 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.77,0:35:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people leave at 600 or more, a higher level.\NEach level, you have an option to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.48,0:35:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes you don't know what's going to happen.\NYou wait and see if you're going to leave or not leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.68,0:35:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.54,0:35:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NGood to see you, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.60,0:35:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry.\NIt's a state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.16,0:35:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay, whatever.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.55,0:35:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is about wolves in sheep's clothing,\Nas you've been talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.50,0:35:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?\NOh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.97,0:36:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're ever disguised as a spiritual aspirant,\Nand if it's ever okay to deal with people under 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.15,0:36:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when you feel like,\Noh, there's a spiritual aspirant,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.49,0:36:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they could be wearing the sheep's clothing of a spiritual aspirant,\Nis that what you're saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.49,0:36:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut inside they're really demonic and evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.79,0:36:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm sure of that.\NAmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.51,0:36:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NIs it, you always warn, stay away from under 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.03,0:36:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay away from under 200.\NI think to avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.39,0:36:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid.\NJesus Christ said don't oppose evil, avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.34,0:36:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had a lot of interesting people come into my life lately,\Nand I have made exceptions because I didn't know how to say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.00,0:36:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I don't know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.38,0:37:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it feels unloving and unkind to say no when somebody is in desperation,\Nand yet it's such a drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.94,0:37:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a test.\NYou have to know how to be able to say no without feeling guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.36,0:37:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a test along the way.\NI said yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.39,0:37:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That was just negative.\NThat was very negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.83,0:37:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I said to the people who were in the room,\Nand I was 법lless in my own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.04,0:37:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to the people,\NI said God, God, a question that I've been asked in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.41,0:37:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a question that I've been asked in my life,\Njust to be able to think that God and I are close,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.71,0:37:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're not the same,\Nthat we're not the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.37,0:37:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have a common purpose,\Nhelp, help, help.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.66,0:37:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the most important thing that I can say is,\NI think people will try to cling to you and hang on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.54,0:37:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the crabs in a pail,\Nthe crabs in the pail,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.74,0:37:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when one tries to get out and starts to go over the tide of the pail,\Nthe other crabs pull them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.23,0:37:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to know when you have to walk on,\Nrelationship with God, what do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.87,0:38:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're right.\NYou can intuitively detect that they really
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.97,0:38:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,mean to pull you down with them in a parasitic dependency,\Nwhich they juice you for your energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.87,0:38:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, they used to be called electric and magnetic.\NThere was a psychic lady in town that was pretty smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.45,0:38:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,She would call them electric and magnetic.\NThe electric would give you energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.38,0:38:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the magnetic would like pull your energy.\NAnd she divided people into those that pull your energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.86,0:38:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and those that give you energy.\NPeople below your own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.38,0:38:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will be pulling energy from you, OK?\NI'm in a pickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.12,0:38:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you try to avoid them.\NYou can, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.75,0:38:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I agonized over it.\NI knew I shouldn't, and I agonized, agonized over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.43,0:39:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right.\NI could not say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.09,0:39:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know what you mean, yep.\NGod knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.16,0:39:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in an extra bedroom, and can't you just\Nlet me board here for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.34,0:39:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you discover they're doing evil incantations over your bed\Nwhile you're sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.55,0:39:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, it's all right.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.05,0:39:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I understand what you're saying.\NA lot of people run into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.76,0:39:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tough one.\NThat's why people go to Al-Anon, you know, because, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.50,0:39:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people go to Al-Anon.\NI was wondering if you had any advice on how
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.78,0:39:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to practice this identification.\NHow to practice this identification with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.28,0:39:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and unconditional love toward the self simultaneously.\NYeah, it's the following all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.28,0:39:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're teaching combined.\NIt's following all the things combined, all of it at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.39,0:40:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the first question?\NHow to practice this identifying with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.62,0:40:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NTo be aware that the functioning of the mind is not the real self.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.38,0:40:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind wants everything.\NIt wants amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.24,0:40:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to be bright.\NIt's self-glorifying, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.14,0:40:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And you disown that as your own reality.\NAnd you say that's the way the ego is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.49,0:40:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And disown that you're identifying with it.\NYou can say, I am what I am despite that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.56,0:40:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite that, not because of that, or not that I am that.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.94,0:40:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the animal nature.\NYou can call it animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.34,0:41:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal nature is greedy, desirous, narcissistic, vain,\Nwants to control, wants to take over the territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.74,0:41:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,wants all the opposite sex.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.61,0:41:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stay compassionate at the same time.\NBut you recognize it's the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.43,0:41:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Those kind of instincts.\NIt always has to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.67,0:41:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to control.\NIt plays king of the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.94,0:41:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture two wolf males, you know.\NI'm my territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.68,0:41:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm my women.\NMy territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.42,0:41:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My women.\NAnd that's the USA and America.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.20,0:41:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the international situation.\NBut there's a part of me which isn't that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.42,0:41:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NIt's bored with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.41,0:41:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Best to just be bored with all that,\Nother than to denounce it as evil or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.95,0:41:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tedious.\NIt's chasing your own tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.50,0:41:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because no matter how much you gain,\Nthere's still more that can be gained.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.52,0:42:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're worth $100 million, you could be worth $100 million.\Ncould be worth $150 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.68,0:42:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're worth $150 million, you could be worth a billion.\NWhen you're worth a billion, you could be worth $100 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.50,0:42:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You could be richer than the Queen of England, you see.\NWhat good will it do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.94,0:42:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only eat one sandwich at a time,\Nsleep in one bed at a time, drive one car at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.24,0:42:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,make love with one person at a time.\NSo it doesn't do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.44,0:42:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All the excess doesn't do much good.\N100 pounds of potatoes is better than one pound.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.87,0:42:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How many can you eat?\NI'm a little nervous, so you have to excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.09,0:42:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have a question that's come to mind many times when I've come before.\NAnd one of your wonderful teachings to include not being spiritually naive
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.77,0:43:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is a big important lesson for me.\NToo much?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.28,0:43:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's either too close or too far.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.88,0:43:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A big question for me is about the spiritual naivete\Nand how important that was for me to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.68,0:43:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a big one for me, all these years of spiritual work.\NOne of the analogies.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.66,0:43:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the analogies you gave about Chamberlain versus Hitler\Nand how Chamberlain went to Hitler and peace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.42,0:43:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that was a couple of times ago you gave us that analogy.\NI had the white paper, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.60,0:43:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.\NAnd so I wonder how one stays integrous in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.90,0:43:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in your life and your everyday comings and goings.\NYou have to work with folks that have calibrations that are not integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.96,0:43:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you give some clues of how one\Ngoes about the world and is able to make good choices
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.77,0:44:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and not change your own level of integrity to deal in the world?\NWell, you try to choose the most integrous pathway you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.07,0:44:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you find yourself in a non-integrous one,\Nyou try to find the most diplomatic way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.21,0:44:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove yourself and to stop identifying with it.\NAnd hold in mind what you do want.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.17,0:44:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold in mind what you do want.\NBecause what you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.10,0:44:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hold in mind that which you would be pleased and desirous of.\NYou hold in mind what you do want and just refuse that which you don't want or leave
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.87,0:44:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NYou can say, I've worn it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.87,0:44:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.20,0:44:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, I've worn it out.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.94,0:44:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Explored it.\NYou've worn it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.61,0:44:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.16,0:44:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,May I have a picture?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.16,0:44:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThey keep him busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.28,0:44:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's like the official photographer.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.82,0:45:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.93,0:45:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins and Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.76,0:45:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I have studied the Course in Miracles, and I'm working on it the second time.\NAnd I work as a nurse practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.44,0:45:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd how do I incorporate my new change of view of the world and people into this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.28,0:45:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,medical world?\NWell, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.76,0:45:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it the way you see it.\NAnd some of it rubs off, and some of it does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.52,0:45:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSome people you can even recommend they try doing the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.45,0:45:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you've seen a lot of people recover from a lot of illnesses.\NYou've got to be careful about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.03,0:45:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't consider you some kind of a proselyte or nut, you know.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.23,0:45:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just utilize it within yourself,\Nand the patients benefit from the fact that you yourself are coming from a higher place, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.97,0:46:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been starting my day with the prayer from the course that I am here because of he who sent me.\NAnd that's been helping me as a guidance system that what I say or what comes out of me isn't just my opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.39,0:46:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, yes.\NSo that's been helping me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.99,0:46:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you do the lesson for the day, and you go about your business,\Nand you choose to be as loving, you know, instead of forgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.89,0:46:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you choose to be as loving as possible, one way of being loving is to choose.\NYou can see forgivingness as an option, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.09,0:46:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.03,0:46:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If people could be better, they would be.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.87,0:46:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.79,0:46:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they're stuck where they are.\NThat's what Jesus said.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.05,0:46:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive them and they know not what they do.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.07,0:46:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.23,0:46:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can forgive them.\NYou don't have to give them the keys to your new car, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.50,0:47:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm moving as fast as I can move.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.60,0:47:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy sister and I are from Seattle, and we're not going to ask any questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.38,0:47:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the most quoted person in our life, I tell you.\NI hope we quote you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.30,0:47:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope we quote you correctly.\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.54,0:47:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NWe'll lose all of our friends after a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.62,0:47:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll get...\NBut I just want to thank you so much for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.08,0:47:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for thanking me.\NOne thing that we've done is we have you on all the time through the night, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.30,0:47:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that whenever we wake up, you know, we hear a little bit and can go back to sleep.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.68,0:47:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSome people do for the music, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.65,0:47:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They like the music, yeah.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.35,0:47:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I do hope that I'm not just brainwashing myself all the time.\NNo, I understand what you're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.09,0:47:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And have some of my own thoughts, because we have you on all the time.\NYou just want...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.43,0:48:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what you want is that energy is all.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.89,0:48:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What you want is the energy.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.95,0:48:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.91,0:48:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted to get your picture.\NWe all do that with certain kinds of music or incense or reminders, symbols, statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.91,0:48:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I could get up as easy.\NI forgot the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.48,0:48:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.48,0:48:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NI'm here to ask you to om, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.08,0:49:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And a picture.\NShe said something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.20,0:49:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NOh, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.53,0:49:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.50,0:49:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lots of questions for you.\NAnd I was wondering if I could spend the next hour with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.03,0:49:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou can.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.03,0:50:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.\NSit right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.59,0:50:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NPut your feet up here and put your bottom there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.96,0:50:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Whisper in my ear.\NOkay, doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.84,0:50:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?\NWhat's up, doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.82,0:50:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want maybe some validation over some doubt I'm having in exploring sort of the\Ninner realms of my psyche in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.76,0:50:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been training in hypnosis, hypnotherapy.\NAnd have been working with regression and going back to different seeming episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.72,0:50:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's like part of me that's doubtful.\NLike there's sort of the witness that's looking over the occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.38,0:50:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you take yourself back to?\NSomething you specify in advance?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.08,0:50:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's with intention and like the cause of something occurring in my life.\NOh, what is that connected with, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.36,0:50:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NWhat is this connected with?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.82,0:51:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And.\NIt's sort of a sense of something coming about, but there's some doubt in.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.70,0:51:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to be literally factual.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.08,0:51:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's naive.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.68,0:51:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be more that it recontextualizes for you.\NSignificance, meaning, and all that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.96,0:51:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe specifics are not necessary, usually.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.72,0:51:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the symbolism of what was and what is now, and you see the connecting thread.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.01,0:51:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIn certain types of past life recall, you're not remembering an event like you're watching a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.72,0:51:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NWhat happens is the actual event begins to rerun all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.72,0:51:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYou know, witnessing or watching something like out there from here, you're in the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.06,0:52:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the movie is happening again with the same sense of reality as it did originally.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.40,0:52:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.19,0:52:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So the experience that.\NSo I was recalling was that I was sort of enslaved by this man, and that I had died,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.69,0:52:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead of returning to maybe the light or, you know, I decided to sort of invade him in a way,\Nlike attach to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.51,0:52:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NDoes that seem like.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.75,0:52:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a possibility, or.\NYeah, it's a possibility, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.23,0:52:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.69,0:52:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.97,0:52:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAppreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.84,0:52:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do all these come from?\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.03,0:52:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.63,0:52:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Doc.\NSusan.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.17,0:52:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NUm, we've come up to ask for a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.77,0:52:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NUh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.26,0:53:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Rob and I, um, have committed our relationship to be in service to each other on our path\Nto God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.36,0:53:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd we would love for you to bless that alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.86,0:53:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can bless, what, your love, your unitedness, and your devotion.\NThat you do it for yourself, for the other, and for God, and for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.08,0:53:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.42,0:53:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.\NI said you'd do that for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.16,0:53:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.90,0:53:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.62,0:54:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOne thing I'd like to express gratitude for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.66,0:54:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd bringing people closer to God, and so much specific explanations on how to get over
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.56,0:54:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so many things.\NBut my question is, I have so many health issues, and I'm wondering, is there a mindset
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.98,0:54:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to certain specific health issues, or a way to get over, to be healed from them?\NWell, we're going to put out a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.66,0:54:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.24,0:54:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NI did a bunch of lectures years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.83,0:54:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Things I understood, things I treated, things that I myself experienced, and the answers\Nthat I found, you know, for whatever good it might be, people have similar things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.66,0:54:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really amazing the number of things you can go through in a lifetime and still survive.\NI mean, as you're, you know, when you put them all end to end, and write them all up,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.54,0:54:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really quite awesome.\NYou know, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.24,0:54:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, between blood clots, and lupus, and migraines, and all this stuff.\NWhere do you get all that negative?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.02,0:54:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, where do you get all that?\NNegative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.50,0:55:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSometimes, because of the speed and the height of your own spiritual evolution, you bring
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.42,0:55:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things up in one lifetime.\NSo how do you get over?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.42,0:55:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You go from here to there.\NYou pull in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.42,0:55:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NEvery karmic whirlwind along the way, and you can slow that down by just being dumb
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.38,0:55:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and not trying to evolve spiritually.\NJust zoning out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.82,0:55:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.46,0:55:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.46,0:55:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your time.\NThank you for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.08,0:55:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Susan.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.08,0:55:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your doctor.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.47,0:55:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to thievery, or something like that.\NAnd you're stationary.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.85,0:55:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lon, from the San Francisco Bay Area.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.85,0:55:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One question.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.56,0:55:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As I promised.\NFirst, you stated in your writings that one can reach the 500 levels in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.56,0:56:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in one lifetime.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.56,0:56:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Does one have to transcend from the low 400s all the way up to the 499s?\NWell, it's not a linear progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.18,0:56:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can jump from 350 right to 510.\NNo stopping off in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.37,0:56:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm making a very serious surrender and seeing things at some great depth.\NSome spiritual passion comes up, and you can jump 150 points in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.03,0:56:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.22,0:56:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, I'm a teacher at an urban middle school, public school.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.22,0:57:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to identify the critical factor to be able to teach the best I can teach.\NTo teach what?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.84,0:57:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.12,0:57:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The critical factor?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.12,0:57:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your willingness to be of service.\NYou see, the student feels your love for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.41,0:57:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you love them, they'll do anything for you.\NKids will do anything if you express that love to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.73,0:57:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not avert.\NYou can't say, kid, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.73,0:57:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll think you're a pedophile.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.14,0:57:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a mentor.\NHe was a professor at the teacher's college who lived across the street from my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.76,0:57:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And he became a great friend.\NAnd I was into entomology, and I had some great specimens.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.12,0:57:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We swapped specimens.\NBut that camaraderie between me as a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.40,0:57:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about 10 or 11 at that time.\NAnd he was a full professor in the Department of Science at the teacher's college.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.56,0:57:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But that lasted me a lifetime.\NAnd in later years, his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.17,0:58:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Who then became an internist.\NHe and myself became friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.17,0:58:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we've been friends forever since.\NAnd so the value of some teacher in your life who allows you to experience the value of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.12,0:58:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say the gift of being myself to the fullest extent I can to this child.\NAnd let him know I appreciate his ambition and his interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.93,0:58:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.93,0:58:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Returning interest.\NI can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.11,0:58:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Atwood would say, boy, that's some specimen you got there.\NWell, my pride would just swell up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.30,0:58:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Luna moth about this big, you know.\NTook me all night in the swamp to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.16,0:59:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All night long in the swamp.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.16,0:59:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know if it's for the highest good to move to Sedona.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.77,0:59:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't just say that like that.\NIt has to be a decision you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.93,0:59:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't know how to answer that for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.03,0:59:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can answer that for her.\NWhat do you want to come to Sedona for?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.58,0:59:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To be around the energy field.\NTo be around what?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.58,0:59:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field.\NFor your own spiritual advancement.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.38,0:59:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, like holy.\NYou mean for your own spiritual advancement?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.38,0:59:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Like holy company?\NSo therefore, what is your question?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.34,0:59:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a ?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.76,0:59:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NTo choose move for because of holy company.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.76,0:59:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat could be higher than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.76,0:59:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.81,0:59:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great motivation.\NThat's why many people came to Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.81,1:00:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They knew there was a certain spiritual energy.\NNot the ooh, la, la, new agey.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.25,1:00:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But the actual.\NBecause even those who are misled are trapped in the glamour of all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a core of reality.\NThere's a core of reality that they really do want spiritual advancement.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.80,1:00:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always try to tell them, try and avoid the amusements along the way.\NJust to save time, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.02,1:00:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.16,1:00:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A great many people came to Sedona for that very reason.\NBecause of some spiritual pathways, some spiritual teacher, because of spiritual friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.89,1:00:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.48,1:01:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one best surrender or transcend joy?\NJoy?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.41,1:01:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy?\NJoy?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.99,1:01:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender or transcend joy?\NWell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.03,1:01:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the back of the mind, there is, depending on your own spiritual trajectory.\NIn this mind, as exquisite as it was, was the knowingness that this too has to be laid down to the old Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.52,1:01:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That came as a knowingness.\NThis too must be laid down to the old Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.44,1:01:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the state, it was the state that Ramakrishna also experienced.\NIt was exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.80,1:01:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the same state.\NAnd I saw that one could get attached to that state.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.44,1:02:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Attached to the being in a state of high joy.\NAnd in fact, it was more than high joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.79,1:02:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ecstasy.\NEcstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.62,1:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Timeless ecstasy.\NAnd in this particular case, there was the knowingness that this too must be laid down,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.00,1:02:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,given, surrendered to the old Lord.\NAnd sometimes, like, the more I push it away, the stronger it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.08,1:02:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't push it away.\NBut.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.81,1:02:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say to push it away.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.81,1:02:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I said become.\NBecome that joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.81,1:02:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Become that ecstasy.\NAnd know that sooner or later, one will need to go beyond even that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.61,1:02:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNo, don't push it away.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.48,1:02:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't resist it.\NBecome it to the fullest extent.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.51,1:03:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When I dance for you, I dance out of ecstasy and joy.\NI don't repel it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.33,1:03:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't refuse it.\NIt's exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.33,1:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful.\NIt's.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.02,1:03:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It does itself.\NIt doesn't require any person to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.53,1:03:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's automatically doing it itself.\NFacing the patterns in the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.53,1:03:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And becoming out of joy and ecstasy, the essence of that pattern.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.53,1:03:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.53,1:03:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThis question comes from Kansas, from my daughter and son-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.56,1:03:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.56,1:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.56,1:03:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.58,1:03:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.58,1:03:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.16,1:03:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.25,1:03:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.25,1:03:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.92,1:03:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.92,1:03:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi!\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.92,1:03:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.92,1:04:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.52,1:04:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't answer this, resist. No, I can't answer it. If it were me, I'd go for it, but I mean, you know, what more do you want?\NWell, that's enough of an answer for them to go for it. They'll go for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.40,1:04:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alaska is so incredibly beautiful, but you have to value the rural and the remote.\NAnd they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.32,1:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.38,1:04:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. They are aware of those limitations.\NYeah. It's a great place to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.31,1:04:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NYou learn how to fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.13,1:04:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think bush planes all over the place.\NThat's right. There's no roads.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.26,1:05:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.50,1:05:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing this spontaneously for the first time without writing this out.\NI've had a lot of deeply held beliefs that I was unaware of from the unconscious that have been profoundly affecting my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.14,1:05:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are surfacing.\NAnd a lot of those are from my experience with my biological father.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.94,1:05:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With your biological father?\NWith my biological father projected onto God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.94,1:05:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh-huh.\NHow do I surrender those?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.46,1:05:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, do you know which ones they are specifically?\NUnforgiving.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.34,1:05:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Unforgiving, uh-huh. Judgmental, yeah.\NAbandoning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.30,1:05:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoning.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.80,1:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Rejecting.\NBut don't see God as a hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.34,1:06:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rejecting.\NRejecting.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.42,1:06:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Rejecting.\NRejecting.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.46,1:06:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, God is not androgenic, so don't identify divinity as masculinity, because that which\Nis beyond gender, that which is the source of the universe is also beyond all gender
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.40,1:06:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or is not going to be this way or that way, so in a way you're talking about anthropomorphic\Ndepictions of God, cast in a paternalistic view, and that's my criticism of old time
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.78,1:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,religion and the Bible and all, is seeing God as some kind of an anthropomorphic projection,\Nso a temper, subject to jealousy and fits and punishing and all this kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.23,1:07:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even realize this, Dr. Williams.\NNo, I don't think that's too advanced in understanding of God, that's a very primitive
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.13,1:07:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,idea.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.91,1:07:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a tribal culture on the other side of the world, thousands of years B.C., and\Nthe concepts were appropriate for the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.48,1:07:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the concept of divinity of the American Indian native culture, much more benign, much\Nmore also feminine, to be the source of the spirit of all of life and its expression as
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.48,1:07:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,nature and divinity and the animal forms.\NYou know, the spirit guides, the spirit guides to the various animal forms are a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.74,1:07:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there are spirit guides for each one, yeah, there are spirit guides for each\None.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.57,1:08:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a condensation of spiritual energy of that animal's nature, and we wrote\Nabout it in Power Versus Force, I think, energy fields, so what this animal knows is a radiation
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.20,1:08:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the knowingness of that field.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.55,1:08:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NSo when it leaves the physical body, its spirit goes to the one spirit, because the animals
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.71,1:08:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all have one spirit, and that's the god of the leopard, or the god of the monkeys, or\Nthe gods, so these various gods, which is typical in Hinduism, those are energy power
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.62,1:08:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,fields, attractor fields.\NThe word I'm on is attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.28,1:08:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat is the collective attractor field of that animal species, and it makes sense to,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.16,1:08:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,again, the pantheon of gods of Hinduism makes sense, because there are energy constellations,\Nyou see, which represent that animal knowingness, that animal way of beingness, and that type
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.26,1:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of animal grace, you see?\NEach animal has its own grace, even though it may look terrible to you, that is its grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.44,1:09:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBetter to eat you, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.60,1:09:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.60,1:09:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.60,1:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So Native American and Hindu pantheons, you know, get the energy field of the, the attractor\Nenergy field of those life forms, and they are valid.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.80,1:09:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They are valid.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.79,1:09:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you don't want to get them mad.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.92,1:09:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll work harder.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.59,1:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWelcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.59,1:10:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, good to see you.\NI wanted to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.04,1:10:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had any thing to say, or any particular advice for me as a young gay man on the spiritual\Npathway.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.02,1:10:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NIt seems very complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.76,1:10:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it does.\NAnd the politicalization of today's world, and the legalities, I grew up to consider
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.49,1:10:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,platonic love a valid.\NIntense, sometimes far more intense than heterosexual love.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.22,1:10:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And some degree of it is innate to being in the service, where the bonding, and the loyalty,\Nand the love of the men for each other can be very, very powerful and very strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.38,1:11:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And I consider that legitimate.\NWhether one gets into sexualization brings up a whole new thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.37,1:11:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The seven deadly sins, one of them is lust.\NTherefore.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.37,1:11:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To surrender the lust aspect, you know, to supplement the lust aspect, try to make it\Nmore of a Hellenic classic, the love between men was celebrated in those days.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.72,1:11:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Celebrated.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.97,1:11:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Platonic love.\NSo, platonic love is an ideal.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.97,1:11:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ideal.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.04,1:11:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it were my own condition, I would strive for that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.04,1:11:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would also use this as maybe an opportunity to transcend something that other men are really\Nstuck in, and that is lust itself, or its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.07,1:12:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you could look at it as an opportunity to let go.\NNow, the way you transcend lust, or any desire, you'll find that every desire, whether this
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.58,1:12:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is for alcohol, for drugs, for sexuality, comes up first as an image in the mind.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.96,1:12:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't first get the thing, you first have an image, and if you're quick enough,\Nyou'll see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.96,1:12:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, no, I don't get an image of it.\NI thought of a drink, it just was in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.96,1:12:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was the thought of a drink.\NWhat happens is the thought of a desire comes up first.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.96,1:12:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can eliminate that thought the instant it's there.\NIf you allow it to linger, it will draw more and more energy, and finally, it will reach
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.96,1:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a point where you cannot say no to it.\NThat's the secret of how to overcome any addiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.90,1:12:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NWhat I see happen with some people, gay people, is they get addicted to sexuality and carnality
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.90,1:12:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake.\NThe downside, then, is to get sucked into sensory pleasure and carnality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.22,1:13:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside is the opportunity to transcend that and deny that, and that's the Hellenic\Ntradition, where the sports figures were the great figures of the time, and where the love
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.44,1:13:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of one man for another was traditional.\NThat's the way I'd hold it, in my own understanding and my own development of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.86,1:13:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Read some Plato.\NRead some Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.99,1:13:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?\NRead some Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.99,1:13:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NPlatonic love means non-sensual, non-you call indulgent of the senses, non-whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.32,1:13:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you call it.\NYou can eat for survival, or you can eat out of gluttony.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.31,1:13:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I see sometimes gay couples fall into what I would call sensual gluttony in the experiential\Nframing of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.31,1:14:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And some I've known for many years, and they're, you know, the same as an ordinary married\Ncouple of any kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.88,1:14:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Helpful, helpful teammates, loyal, and forever.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.49,1:14:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.20,1:14:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No questions.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.24,1:14:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NNow that I'm here, I know a lot less than I used to.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.84,1:14:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NI know a lot less than I did before I moved here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.57,1:14:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I seem to be reacting to everything in my life.\NI have my little mental commentaries going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.57,1:14:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I react emotionally to everything, and I can't tell.\NI look at things, I can't tell what's real, and what's just the way I'm interpreting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.57,1:14:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just need a little help getting it in context, because I'm just nothing but reactions\Nlately.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.70,1:14:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally reacting to everything?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.70,1:14:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo how do you become detached?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.70,1:15:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you emotionalize everything?\NWhy do I?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.70,1:15:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.62,1:15:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's just a habit.\NYou can't just look at a dead mouse on the floor and say, oh, it's a dead mouse.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.13,1:15:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender the theatrics and the drama.\NStop being a drama queen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.44,1:15:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't have to dramatize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.44,1:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.60,1:15:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to experience a thing and see what it is, you don't have to dramatize it.\NSometimes people get to thinking that, oh, it's a dead mouse.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.63,1:15:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.63,1:15:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.63,1:15:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.63,1:15:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.63,1:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.63,1:15:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.63,1:15:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou don't have to be thinking that that's their duty as a woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.63,1:15:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to dramatize.\NNo, you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.63,1:15:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be detached and cool and cold and say, that's a mouse, so what?\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.63,1:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll pick them up.\NWhat's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.63,1:15:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to scream and faint and fall on the floor.\NIt's not all about me, probably.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.43,1:15:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NEverything that happens is probably not all about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.43,1:15:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.43,1:16:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're really complaining about is sort of excessive emotionalizing.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.43,1:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I pray to God to help you transcend emotionalizing.\NPray to become more detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.46,1:16:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectualize it and mentalize it.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.74,1:16:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizing it is coming up through the solar plexus.\NMentalizing it is bringing it up to the head.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.49,1:16:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So try to bypass the solar plexus and put it in the form of thought.\NThought.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.51,1:16:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about it, not what do you feel about it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.11,1:16:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't care what you feel about it.\NDo you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.03,1:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I've noticed.\NThey really don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.91,1:16:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You like this?\NEverybody says, yeah, that's well.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.66,1:16:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I don't like that.\NOh, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.51,1:16:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now try doing, force the energy up, you know, from the solar plexus up into the mind.\NThe thinkingness chakra.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.79,1:16:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thing.\NThe thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.22,1:17:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To mentalize about it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.50,1:17:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Write a little mental thing about it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.72,1:17:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a practice.\NIt's just habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.87,1:17:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnd it follows family traditions, cultural traditions, and you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.97,1:17:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NCultural styles.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.76,1:17:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Men don't have that problem.\NThe plan is, don't you have any feelings?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.79,1:17:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's what I was thinking about, Henrietta.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.99,1:17:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten days ago when I came here, I got direction from you that I haven't been able to get in four years for the treatment of the lower astral attacks on my daughter.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.15,1:17:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted you to tell me about that.\NAnd I wanted to thank you, Andrea, Dr. Kallenbach, and Susan, for the support.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.15,1:17:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a psychiatrist.\NWe're going this next week in Texas to see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.43,1:18:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The astral attacks have been very hard.\NIt's a biochemistry, it's a problem in brain chemistry and biochemical.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.89,1:18:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very easy to fix.\NIt's very easy to fix.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.40,1:18:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched her go into an attack on Friday, and for the very first time, she started to say, no, I rebuke you, and I refute you.\NAnd all she could get out was no, and she got stuck into the state.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.38,1:18:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What would have lasted five minutes only lasted a minute.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.88,1:18:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd all she kept saying was no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.82,1:18:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But in her mind, she was thinking, I rebuke you, and I refuse you in the name of Jesus Christ.\NSo she wanted to come meet this man that finally believed her that she's not crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.14,1:18:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou refute it, and you also biochemically block it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.38,1:18:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\NBecause anything wrong in the nervous system, the entity will use that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.56,1:18:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\NLike unconsciousness, brain injury, drunkenness, those, that's the, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.21,1:19:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like the human becomes vulnerable then.\NSo you offset it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.67,1:19:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So pharmacology, you're doing all the right things.\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.17,1:19:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NShe wanted to say thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.07,1:19:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing all the right things.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.53,1:19:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,May we get a photo?\NShe'll be better.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.81,1:19:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be all right.\NThese things can be awful when they happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.71,1:19:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But also, very often, you can find the solution, and the solution is often very simple.\NYou know, you can turn on a lot of these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.01,1:19:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A half a milligram a day of prolixin can turn it on and turn it off.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.13,1:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Something simple like that.\NSure enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.34,1:19:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All on the scissor, that way.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.94,1:19:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab a photo, dear.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.44,1:19:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can perforate an ulcer and take one tablet of something rather than the ulcer cures.\NI mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.66,1:19:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything.\NEverything is physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.18,1:19:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take care of all three at the same time.\NEverything is physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.69,1:20:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You hit it on all three levels.\NShe'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.04,1:20:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get any negative feeling around here.\NShe's going to be better.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.38,1:20:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Harkins.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.82,1:20:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you hold my hands while I ask this question?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.08,1:20:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOften when I meditate, I'm beginning to become deeply relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.87,1:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My neck will go backwards like this as I relax, or it'll go to the side and contort like this.\NI'm wondering if it's safe for me to let it do that, because that happens at the same time that,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.19,1:20:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the meditative state is deepening.\NIs it safe for me to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.28,1:20:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can refuse it.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.57,1:20:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens is when I change my body back to being upright, I lose the progress\Nthat I had made the previous, like, four or five weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.63,1:21:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, try breathing it up to a higher chakra.\NKeep breathing it up to the crown chakra, the energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.11,1:21:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep breathing the energy up to the crown chakra.\NI don't understand how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.96,1:21:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You breathe.\NYou picture the energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.96,1:21:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the energy stuck when you're having this problem?\NI don't understand how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.62,1:21:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the energy stuck when you're having this problem?\NYou're afraid to stop what?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.25,1:21:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My body from going, like, so my neck will go backwards like this, because I've heard\Nthat people go into psychotic states sometimes when their neck goes back like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.40,1:21:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm wondering whether it's okay.\NIs that not so?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.86,1:21:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.63,1:21:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt's sometimes, and it's often, like, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.44,1:21:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.44,1:22:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you want to do is when you feel that in there, picture it going up.\NPicture it going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.77,1:22:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo your brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.51,1:22:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo the crown chakra.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.51,1:22:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo don't concentrate on fixing the physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.51,1:22:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrate on the breathing.\NWell, it'll fix itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.80,1:22:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll fix itself, yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.20,1:22:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.54,1:22:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDr. Hawkins?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.54,1:22:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMay I touch your feet in gratitude?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.54,1:22:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.54,1:22:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you please touch my head again?\NAnd what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.45,1:22:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Touch your head.\NWhatever you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.45,1:22:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.52,1:22:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It serves.\NIt's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.35,1:22:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleasure.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.02,1:22:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.02,1:22:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.02,1:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.44,1:23:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.44,1:23:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is for you to be a servant, My встречe Servante, O Lord.\NI give thanks for your divine devotion, your love for God, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.92,1:23:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat is a tradition from India.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.00,1:23:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.49,1:23:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot to touch my head.\NGod bless you!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.14,1:23:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God blesses you now!\NThis is the Indian culture, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.28,1:23:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI came all the way just to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.18,1:23:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so important for me to do it.\NYes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.14,1:23:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And last time I requested that you transmit no mind to me,\Nand you said it's been automatically done.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.60,1:23:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it already.\NOh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.50,1:23:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay a little farther away from that.\NNot so close to the mic.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.62,1:23:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, that's better.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.76,1:24:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, you already have that energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.72,1:24:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.04,1:24:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's verify for her sake.\NThe energy field that you seek is already within your aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.76,1:24:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYeah, you got it last time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.70,1:24:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you did that last time.\NI just want to know if there's any real progress that I've made.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.32,1:24:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NThere are a lot of experiences I have where I just don't have any personal self,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.96,1:24:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, since the last year.\NAnd I just feel like, who am I?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.50,1:24:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I kind of?\NNo, you're looking for answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.62,1:24:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NYou have precipitated by your decision and by your will a certain process.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.62,1:24:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's not up to you to question the process.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.07,1:24:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.43,1:24:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get stupid and fall flat on the ground, that's the way the process is going.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.63,1:24:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go into a state of ecstasy, you have to put up with it.\NThat's the way it's going.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.03,1:25:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd so sometimes, you know, I find it silly to use the personal word, personal I,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.35,1:25:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and because I know it's not real anymore.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.84,1:25:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows this kind of word.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.14,1:25:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, you become, what happens is speaking more and more in the third person.\NSome people complain that I write that way, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.64,1:25:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened, you know, and that happened.\NIt's like a third person report.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.97,1:25:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire came up to ride the bicycle and then the skill arose.\NI don't say the desire came up immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.11,1:25:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To ride the bicycle, the desire came up to learn how to ride a bicycle\Nand out of that, the bicycling skill arose.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.77,1:25:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like happening of its own spontaneously.\NYou don't need to constantly put the pronoun in.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.16,1:25:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAs you eliminate narcissism, the pronoun disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.08,1:26:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that phenomena are happening.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.82,1:26:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo sometimes, you know, it doesn't quite work when you're sitting in a dinner party or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.32,1:26:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in what?\NIt doesn't work when you're in a dinner party.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.08,1:26:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NSo what to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.20,1:26:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see the body starts to eat and enjoy the food.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.57,1:26:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the body doing that.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.79,1:26:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NNot your nose, not your ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.77,1:26:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe senses are seeking gratification.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.01,1:26:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you witness the senses seeking gratification.\NAnd you know that's part of your animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.13,1:26:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NAnd without that, you would die.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.65,1:26:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get hungry and eat, you die.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.88,1:26:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the price of life is putting up with one's animal nature.\NAnd you don't have to call it I.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.88,1:26:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo I can use, I can refrain from using the word I.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.98,1:26:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.06,1:26:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NEven in a social gathering.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.26,1:27:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a certain skill.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.12,1:27:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.56,1:27:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming though, you know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.08,1:27:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,On its own.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.86,1:27:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo be polite, you use certain pronouns.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.40,1:27:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.68,1:27:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NBut.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.24,1:27:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't bring my level of consciousness down, will it?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.90,1:27:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo, you won't get dumber and dumber.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.70,1:27:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They have said I can only ask one question.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.94,1:27:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But may I ask one more?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.39,1:27:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If all the actions of the past, if all the actions of the past.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.28,1:27:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave an impression forever.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.00,1:27:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.05,1:27:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What role.\NWhat role does atonement or the earning of good karma or the undoing of bad karma play?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.28,1:28:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you evolve.\NThat's how you evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.06,1:28:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have a karmic debt, when you repay it, then your energy.\NI always liken it to a magnetic field, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.00,1:28:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're like little iron filings.\NAnd all, every decision you make affects the polarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.58,1:28:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One end is negative, the other end is positive, see?\NSo every time you say yes, oh, I'll forgive them, he didn't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.68,1:28:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The iron filing moves a little more in the positive direction.\NAnd you say, well, I hate him.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.74,1:28:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think he's terrible.\NNow you move a little bit more in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.62,1:28:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So your little iron filing is like constantly moving in the field of gravitational field\Nof the infinite field of consciousness, which is infinitely powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.14,1:28:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't need an arbitrary God who rewards.\NYou or gets mad at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.24,1:29:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the automatic consequence of that which you are.\NTherefore, the justice of God is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.70,1:29:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only be in an infinitely powerful magnetic field exactly where you should be.\NSo every time you forgive somebody, your magnetic polarity moves a little more this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.36,1:29:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You move a little more towards God.\NSo moving towards God is of your own inner consent.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.10,1:29:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So God doesn't force anybody to do anything.\NSo may I give you the example?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.82,1:29:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't very kind to my son when he was little.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.44,1:29:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And but I understand that now.\NAnd I'm being as loving as I possibly can be to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.90,1:29:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've explained it to him that, look, I didn't know what I was doing then.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.66,1:29:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sorry.\NSo does that original action still have an effect forever?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.76,1:29:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you can do.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.30,1:29:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So be it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.33,1:29:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've addressed it.\NSo you had a limitation at one time.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.17,1:29:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize this.\NYou had a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.79,1:30:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm taking so long.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.21,1:30:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know why you had that limitation either.\NGood God.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.37,1:30:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got a bus parked out in front there?\NA bus?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.55,1:30:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.\NOkay, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.93,1:30:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought something for you.\NOh, thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.15,1:30:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who looks just like you.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.04,1:30:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to save this, honey.\NYou put this right here, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.22,1:30:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThat's for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.24,1:30:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.\NYeah, very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.28,1:30:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.28,1:30:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.88,1:30:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.98,1:30:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll love is God's love.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.44,1:31:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.54,1:31:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No squeeze on the merchandise.\NThat's where they have that beautiful island they're building there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.20,1:31:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd they're cute.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.19,1:31:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.12,1:31:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,People from places like Dubai, they go, oh, yeah.\NA billion, billion dollar extension of the building of the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.16,1:31:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They go, uh-huh.\NAnd you're going to have the Queen Mary.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.36,1:31:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They go, uh-huh.\NWhat do you mean, uh-huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.40,1:31:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Queen Mary, for God's sake.\NDubai is an interesting country.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.52,1:31:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you once again on behalf of everyone.\NYour presence is truly a blessing to us all here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.84,1:32:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My question for you is my experience thus far is that there's a depth and a breadth to consciousness,\Nwhich you normally don't go into in the books.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.34,1:32:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But, for example, we have a relationship consciousness.\NWe have a space spiritual consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.72,1:32:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a.\NWe have a professional consciousness, and that all these things play a part.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.71,1:32:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that something that you'd care to comment on or write about?\NThey're not different consciousnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.61,1:32:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a consciousness of a certain level will express itself this way in this situation\Nand this way in this situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.01,1:32:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A person with a different level of consciousness would express themselves differently in the\Nsame situations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.13,1:32:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're not different.\NThey're how that one person responds to all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.40,1:32:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees them as opportunity or resents them.\NHis obligations depends on how he sees it, or he sees it as a chance for camaraderie and good naturedness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.21,1:32:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.45,1:33:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's good for General Motors is good for the country.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.03,1:33:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we used to say when I grew up.\NWhat's good for General Motors is good for the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.84,1:33:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That was what we grew up with.\NWe're going to quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.75,1:33:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.27,1:33:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When we pray to the Lord, does the Lord have to be a specific and an exclusive avatar?\NI don't think so, because you know what you mean by it, and the Lord knows what you mean by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.82,1:33:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God's smart enough to know that he's Lord, and that you're trying to reach him.\NI think that your intention already sets the level.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.87,1:33:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention is already known.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.09,1:33:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.22,1:34:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention is unmistakable.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.38,1:34:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NGood to be with you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.76,1:34:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NLately, I'm crying.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.40,1:34:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the way up here, I've been reading the rest of this book, and part of the Yoga\NVesastha, and Chorus of Miracles, and it seems like the thing for me to do next is to stop
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.68,1:34:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.71,1:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's illegal in certain parts of the world.\NBut the first fear that comes up is that, Neil, you're not ready to do that yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.22,1:34:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To give up thinking?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.48,1:34:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd I don't want to, you know, get impatient and then come to a place where I've failed.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.32,1:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get a chance to give up thinking, by all means, take it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.06,1:35:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can't get ahead of myself then.\NIf you get a chance to give up thinking, do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.59,1:35:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NEverything from that point on is autonomous.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.37,1:35:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to think about what to say to you, do I?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.47,1:35:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes right up.\NI don't have to think about being here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.39,1:35:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to think about that thing.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.55,1:35:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NJoin me.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.98,1:35:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up thinking.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.82,1:35:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.82,1:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NA bad habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.20,1:35:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI've been on the path for a lot of years, and I've had a lot of growth.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.89,1:35:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the past year, I think it's really been coming apart at the seams.\NAnd I've really found that a lot of it has been, like, self-serving.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.77,1:35:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've been, like, throwing myself into the path to avoid dealing with issues and,\Nyou know, with spiritual courage and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.59,1:36:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.41,1:36:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they've really come up to be dealt with, and they're not going anywhere.\NAnd, like, as I've been facing this, it's like, wow, I'm just, like, a really broken person.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.62,1:36:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you are.\NYou're a mess.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.68,1:36:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI just feel like...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.28,1:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a mess.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.70,1:36:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd I feel like I failed you as a student.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.84,1:36:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.\NAnd I feel like...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.54,1:36:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, seriously, though, like...\NYou come and made a mess out of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.68,1:36:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.34,1:36:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like, even though I see it, it's like,\Nthere's just a weakness in my own will to, like, get through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.76,1:36:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're expecting some kind of linear discipline progression of things.\NIt doesn't happen that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.16,1:36:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You go from chaos to collapse to failure to jubilation and then discouragement and then...\NSo, there's no way you can rate whether you're making progress or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.81,1:36:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.17,1:37:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When you finally make real progress,\Nthe question doesn't even...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.11,1:37:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The question doesn't even arise whether you're making progress.\NSo, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.56,1:37:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it's your intention and your alignment,\Nand the rest is not up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.04,1:37:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think that's part that really worries me,\Nis, like, what are my intentions?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.64,1:37:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of it seems so self-serving a lot of the time.\NSelf-serving like what?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.28,1:37:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Worshiping worldly success, material success,\Nposition in the world, special...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.10,1:37:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those are all things you acknowledge is going on within yourself.\NAnd you say that's normal for a certain age.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.42,1:37:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And each of those things, maybe you'll have to live it through a bit to decide.\NThere's nothing wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.49,1:37:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing wrong with it.\NI think in the Bible it says,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.25,1:37:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want worldly success.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.43,1:38:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just that a rich man can't get through the eye of the needle, that's all.\NYou have a shortage of poverty.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.09,1:38:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe's suffering from a poverty shortage.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.34,1:38:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.04,1:38:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NSee, if you weren't okay, you would.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.62,1:38:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be worrying about it.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.34,1:38:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI know, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.28,1:38:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan Hurd.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.86,1:38:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come from Dublin to see you, so I'm very pleased to be here.\NDublin, Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.76,1:38:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.\NYou thought it was in Iowa, not in Iowa.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.27,1:38:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She thought Dublin was in Iowa.\NIn Iowa.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.24,1:38:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, go ahead.\NMy question is, it has changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.20,1:39:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It has changed as I was standing up there.\NYou calibrated homeopathy in truth versus falsehood as 200 and over the years, I'm a medical physician
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.28,1:39:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as well, and over the years I've had a lot of contact with homeopaths who have had miraculous\Nresults with homeopathy where I know that ordinary medicine wouldn't have been able
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.54,1:39:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to affect.\NSo I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.54,1:39:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?\NI'm wondering, how come it calibrates at 200?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.20,1:39:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.20,1:39:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't calibrate it.\NOh, I didn't calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.20,1:39:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Homeopathy?\NI didn't make it be that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.20,1:39:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably talking about the scientific theory of it.\NIs that what you calibrated?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.72,1:39:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This week's newspapers are full of deaths by homeopaths doing liposuction, five or six\Nof them losing their licenses from not knowing what they can do and what they can't do.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.22,1:39:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you talk about public image in this week's Arizona Republic, it's not so great.\NWhat aspect of homeopathy did you calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.11,1:39:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just talked about homeopathy.\NHomeopathy as a theory, you see, as a...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.75,1:40:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Any practice in certain practitioner's hands is excellent.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.49,1:40:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The same practice in an idiot's hands is, you know, terrible, so homeopathy as a field\Nof science.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.45,1:40:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Homeopathy as a field of science doesn't measure up rationally.\NThe effects of it, though, are...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.18,1:40:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about two different things.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.30,1:40:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do homeopathy.\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.37,1:40:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 200.\N205.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.37,1:40:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at 200.\NHomeopathy is 200, so that means the result is more likely intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.07,1:40:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention.\NThe intention of the patient, the intention of the doctor is probably going to bring about.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.52,1:40:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That has to do with the law of similars, does it not?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.90,1:40:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo let's do the law of similars.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.90,1:40:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of similars calibrates over 200, is this?\N205.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.82,1:40:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,210.\N205.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.37,1:40:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the law of similars is about 205.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.57,1:40:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me why.\NYeah, I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.37,1:40:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any money in the market, do I?\NYeah, yeah, I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.37,1:41:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any position about homeopathy.\NAll right, I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.37,1:41:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.37,1:41:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm suffering from an incurable disease, I want to see everybody, including every\Nhomeopath in town.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.50,1:41:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.50,1:41:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Western medicine, like, calibrates at 450, 460.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.50,1:41:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Western medicine.\N460, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.50,1:41:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\N440.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.50,1:41:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,440.\N440.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.87,1:41:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic medicine.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.87,1:41:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.87,1:41:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N440.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.87,1:41:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic medicine.\N440.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.87,1:41:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NClinical medicine.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.87,1:41:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,445.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.80,1:41:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.25,1:41:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.25,1:41:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NNo, just because .
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.04,1:41:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.25,1:41:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that.\NThat's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.25,1:41:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not negative.\NI'm talking about it's effective.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.25,1:41:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not negative.\NIt's not negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.25,1:41:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be more effective than a lot of orthodox medicine, especially for\Nchronic disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.25,1:42:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on how vast your experience is.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.79,1:42:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say you were .\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.66,1:42:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI think your dedication to the patient carries more weight than the mechanics of what you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.76,1:42:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,give them.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.76,1:42:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.76,1:42:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThere are a lot of very dedicated homeopaths, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.76,1:42:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSome doctors can get more cures with distilled water than others can with the world's best
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.76,1:42:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,medicines.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.76,1:42:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.76,1:42:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.70,1:42:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We both .\NI believe you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.70,1:42:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NWe've both seen homeopathic physicians .
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.70,1:42:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.70,1:42:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When something ails me, I'm going to see everybody from top to bottom.\NChiropractor, homeopath, physician, surgeon.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.45,1:42:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you want me to do?\NAnybody got anything crucial that you can make short?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.45,1:42:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to hurry up.\NYou can't spend forever coming up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.02,1:42:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.\NNow.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.15,1:42:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Real quick.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.41,1:43:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.64,1:43:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.11,1:43:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.11,1:43:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.34,1:43:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.34,1:43:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.34,1:43:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.43,1:43:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.43,1:43:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.32,1:43:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.93,1:43:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUp.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.12,1:43:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NUm.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.12,1:43:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Up.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.12,1:43:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NKeep it short and sweet.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.12,1:43:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.12,1:43:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NMy father, just last month, I bring my father to a house for Alzheimer and my
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.12,1:43:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,spouse also bring her mother to Alzheimer's place.\NYou know what he's saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.31,1:43:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alzheimer.\NAlzheimer's.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.11,1:43:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAlzheimer's.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.11,1:43:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alzheimer's got its Alzheimer.\NAlzheimer.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.11,1:43:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.11,1:43:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.11,1:43:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\N. . Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.18,1:43:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring your father and your mother there.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.58,1:44:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, is it a nightmare for them?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.66,1:44:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.54,1:44:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Only for you.\NOnly for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.80,1:44:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe suffering is on the part of the witness,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.14,1:44:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not on the part of the Alzheimer patient.\NSo we don't have to worry about them?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.50,1:44:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThey are taken care of?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.66,1:44:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I've checked that out extensively.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.84,1:44:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the only doctor who was willing to go to the nursing homes\Nin the whole Yavapai County.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.46,1:44:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I get through with seeing patients in Periscope,\Nand I then hit every nursing home in the county all the way home.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.12,1:44:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over again, it was always the same.\NThe family was upset by the Alzheimer patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.06,1:44:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would interview the Alzheimer patient.\NI'd say, how are you today?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.04,1:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello, dearie, I'm fine.\NYou got any complaints today?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.52,1:44:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIs the food all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.08,1:44:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're very nice to me.\NConsistently, I got that from, I would say, 100% of the patients.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.39,1:44:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBut are their soul out of their body?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.23,1:44:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they gone?\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.02,1:45:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not there.\NThey are not there?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.90,1:45:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThe spirit has already gone over to the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.58,1:45:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The body stays here.\NThe family gets upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.80,1:45:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask the patient, you know, if I ask the patient, how are you today?\NOh, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.98,1:45:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they treat you here?\NThey're very nice to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.78,1:45:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I have never heard a complaint.\NAll the sobbing and maudling and carrying on and drama is the family.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.60,1:45:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the family drama.\NOh, poor old daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.72,1:45:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lost his mind.\NAnd I say to dad, how are you, dad?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.47,1:45:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, fine.\NWhy are you asking me?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.62,1:45:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just wondering since you've been here a little while.\NOh, I have, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.86,1:45:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.\NSo, only the envelope stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.36,1:45:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.36,1:45:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God takes care of them.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.28,1:45:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Alzheimer's is painless.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.63,1:45:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just bring you something.\NA sweet maple syrup from Montreal.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.63,1:45:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NTo enjoy with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.63,1:46:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Montreal.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.63,1:46:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the real stuff.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.63,1:46:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat's the real stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.35,1:46:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.\NThat's the real stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.35,1:46:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.35,1:46:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.35,1:46:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the suffering with Alzheimer's is in the witness, not the subject.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.35,1:46:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard anyone complain.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.35,1:46:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they do complain, it's not due to the Alzheimer's, it's due to something else.\NI was just wondering if you would calibrate that book for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.63,1:46:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't want to.\NNo, I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.39,1:46:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NI figured it would be fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.18,1:46:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll tell you.\NThere's too much feedback.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.38,1:46:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NEverybody has to keep their mouth shut or what they know to themself.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.61,1:46:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If I calibrate this, what's going to happen is it's going to be on the internet within\N24 hours and 82 people will object to what's being said, and I've learned the hard way
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.89,1:47:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not to do it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.89,1:47:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you anyway, Doctor.\NNobody can keep their own counsel anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.77,1:47:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIs it relevant to no one's own calibration, and if so, why?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.57,1:47:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it what?\NRelevant to no one.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.78,1:47:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's not really very helpful, no.\NYou know, if you look at the levels of consciousness, you'll intuit approximately where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.10,1:47:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou're either angry all the time, or you're flat or disinterested, or you feel depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.21,1:47:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look where I am.\NWhere am I on the thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.21,1:47:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NAnd there's ways, you know, you can test kinesiology yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.21,1:47:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can say, you know, there's a closed ring finger, you know.\NThe other way is to just hold a bunch of heavy dictionaries and say, my consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.38,1:48:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 200.\NAnd if it is, you'll see the weight, the books weigh something.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.70,1:48:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My consciousness level is over 300.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.88,1:48:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My consciousness level is over 800.\NThe simplest way is you'll notice that your strength, your strength fluctuates.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.12,1:48:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So with a little practice, you can do it all by yourself, just lifting books.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.00,1:48:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo it's just so you'll know that, because your level of...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.00,1:48:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.00,1:48:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.40,1:48:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Enthusiasm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.78,1:48:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,400 is more hard.\N400 is reading a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.77,1:48:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The 300 is being a volunteer fireman.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.77,1:48:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just sort of sense where you are.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.78,1:48:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou just sort of sense it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.42,1:49:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You just keep going straight ahead no matter what.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.83,1:49:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.18,1:49:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHave you found in a love relationship between a man and a woman that there needs to be
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.00,1:49:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,some range of...\NConsciousness level for it to be enduring?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.18,1:49:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't noticed that.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.18,1:49:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are quite the spirit can get along with each other.\NLook at Socrates and his wife, Zantippe.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.85,1:49:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NSo it could be a wide range, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.17,1:49:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, they...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.17,1:49:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMost couples will accommodate to each other and balance it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.80,1:49:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's too far out of line, that relationship won't last, you know.\NWon't last.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.80,1:49:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.53,1:49:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you learn from each other either way, you know.\NShe's back.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.94,1:50:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to cost you a dollar now.\NFlippo.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.27,1:50:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you, George.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.46,1:50:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all done.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.65,1:50:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to run faster.\NYou're too slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.65,1:50:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you guys so slow over there?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.68,1:50:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dr. Hawkins.\NI just wanted to sit in front of you and tell you thank you and I love you and God bless
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.68,1:50:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you for everything you've done for me.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.68,1:50:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NYou've transformed my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.68,1:50:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you for your love.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.68,1:50:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.93,1:50:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my pleasure.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.93,1:50:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly the same.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.93,1:50:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThat's my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.93,1:50:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless.\NGod bless.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.90,1:50:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NWe're saving dessert for the end here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.90,1:50:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.48,1:50:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you very much for your lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.48,1:50:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhat I got was when you dealt with your demons, that moment of despair, what you got was
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.48,1:50:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the way out was to verify the sanctity of your own life.\NDid I get that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.12,1:51:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you ...\NWell, no, that came as a greater understanding later on.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.12,1:51:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're referring to now.\NWell, how do you recommend verifying the sanctity of your own life?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.90,1:51:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a good way to get that?\NVerify it?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.90,1:51:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou don't have to verify it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.90,1:51:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just take my word for it.\NNothing exists without except by divine ordinance.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.90,1:51:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing exists without divine ordinance.\NConsequently, you exist only as a consequence of divine ordinance.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.51,1:51:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NUnless you're capable of spontaneous combustion or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.39,1:51:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAll that exists does so by virtue of divine grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.74,1:51:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine grace, which is called divine ordinance.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.34,1:52:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I hug everyone in this room.\NAnd I give thanks to almighty God for the gift of all of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.34,1:52:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget that we are all one.\NThat we come into this world together, you know, over a couple decades.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.47,1:52:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In my time dimension, that's the same time.\NOver 50 years or so, it's the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.47,1:52:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We all come in together.\NAnd we all leave together.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.47,1:52:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all do this as a unison.\NWe all do this as a unison.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.47,1:52:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NAnd the fear of death is the fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.47,1:52:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fear of death is really not, is the fear of separation.\NI told you about this during World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.66,1:52:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And this mine was going to go off.\NAnd he said, what if it goes off?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.66,1:52:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll die.\NAnd I said, well, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.66,1:52:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, what will happen if it explodes?\NAnd I said, well, we'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.66,1:53:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looked at me and said, yeah.\NBecause he got.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.08,1:53:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't die alone.\NWe will die together.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.11,1:53:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So look at the, I want you to get rid of the fear of death.\NIt's not a fear of dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.11,1:53:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fear of being alone.\NWell, being committed to a group like this is not possible to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.11,1:53:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NIt is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.11,1:53:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So none of us are ever going to be separated.\NIt's not a fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.11,1:53:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fear of separation.\NThat's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.11,1:53:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NSo anyway, God bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.11,1:53:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I give thanks.\NYou are God's gift to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.11,1:53:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, God.\NAnd the world's lucky that we're here, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.55,1:53:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When we give them the bill.\NSaving the bill, the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.76,1:54:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,100 trillion trillion dollars.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.76,1:54:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm submitting a bill.\NAll right.
